results.name: Amicable 5-tuples: (x1,...,x5) such that sigma(x1)=...=sigma(x5)=x1+...+x5. Groups of 5 subsequent terms list the five members in increasing size.
comment: The 5-tuple starting with 53542288800 was given by _Donovan Johnson_. The common value of sigma(x) is 294821130240.

A still larger example (227491164588441600, 228507506351308800, 229862628701798400, 230878970464665600, 243752632794316800), probably the first one to be published, had been found by _Yasutoshi Kohmoto_ in 2008, cf. link to SeqFan post.
There are different definitions for amicable k-tuples, cf. link to MathWorld.
